WEBVTT

00:00.738 --> 00:09.068
It's a real privilege to be speaking to you today and I just pray that God will really touch your hearts through what we hear this morning.

00:09.908 --> 00:17.037
I'm going to be speaking about Moses and he was the most incredible man.

00:17.077 --> 00:21.121
Films have been made about him, stories have been told.

00:21.181 --> 00:25.266
He was at incredible, someone who

00:25.730 --> 00:37.966
took 2.4 million people or maybe even 3 million people out of slavery in Egypt and threw on their journey towards the promised land.

00:38.787 --> 00:43.914
And so he is a man of faith, a man of power.

00:43.934 --> 00:50.002
And this morning we're going to be looking at the journey he had to do

00:50.434 --> 01:00.028
as he began to step into that role and the things that he struggled with and hopefully we can learn some things for ourselves too.

01:01.090 --> 01:04.915
Lord, we just thank you for your presence here this morning.

01:05.636 --> 01:12.847
We thank you for your word, which is so powerful and brings so much joy and help to us.

01:13.208 --> 01:20.338
Lord, we just pray that we'll be able to take in those bits that you really want us to focus on this morning.

01:20.578 --> 01:21.820
in Jesus' name.

01:22.461 --> 01:22.901
Amen.

01:22.961 --> 01:31.213
So Moses was born at a very difficult time and he was born in Egypt.

01:31.914 --> 01:42.929
And it was a time when the Pharaoh was really feeling the pressure of having all these amazing Hebrew Jewish people living in his land.

01:43.410 --> 01:49.138
They were multiplying quickly and he began to feel really threatened by them.

01:49.314 --> 01:54.561
And so he decided, first of all, to make slaves of them.

01:55.482 --> 02:04.094
And secondly, when that didn't seem to have much effect, he commanded the midwives to kill all the baby boys as they were being born.

02:04.995 --> 02:09.321
And this is the time that Moses was born.

02:10.062 --> 02:15.810
And his parents kept him for about three months, and then they knew they'd be found.

02:16.490 --> 02:19.154
And in the end,

02:19.298 --> 02:21.360
that would be the end of their baby.

02:21.440 --> 02:32.751
So they made a little basket for him and put him in the Nile and left him there with only his sister keeping a knife from the banks of the river.

02:32.791 --> 02:35.253
And it was an incredible story.

02:35.333 --> 02:48.946
I'm sure you know it where the princess, the Muthis, comes down and she's bathing and she hears this baby crying and she goes to pick him up and something about that baby

02:49.250 --> 02:58.403
connects with her and she decides that she will take him as her own son as she hadn't got any children so far.

02:59.124 --> 03:10.701
And so Moses was brought up by his adopted mother in a foreign land, foreign to his own family anyway in Egypt.

03:11.522 --> 03:14.546
And Steven says,

03:15.202 --> 03:19.188
in his account of Moses in Acts chapter seven.

03:19.829 --> 03:29.383
Moses was educated in all the wisdom of the Egyptians and was powerful in word and in speech and action.

03:30.645 --> 03:36.474
So he was brought up completely differently to the rest of his family.

03:37.115 --> 03:44.466
He had privilege, he had education and he had a lot of charm about him too.

03:44.834 --> 03:55.909
The Jewish historian Flavius Josephus describes Moses as being particularly intelligent, he says.

03:55.970 --> 04:02.919
Now Moses' understanding became superior to his age, far beyond that standard.

04:03.200 --> 04:10.950
And when he was taught, he discovered greater quickness of apprehension than was usual at his age.

04:11.491 --> 04:13.554
And his actions at that time

04:13.666 --> 04:17.130
promise greater when he should come to the age of a man.

04:17.190 --> 04:24.199
God did also give him that tallness when he was about three years old as was wonderful.

04:26.061 --> 04:29.786
So he was an outstanding child right from the beginning.

04:32.589 --> 04:43.442
Josephus also describes a military campaign which Moses led in his, I don't know when he was 20s or whatever,

04:44.034 --> 04:56.972
And he led the Egyptian army in a battle to kind of keep them safe because the Ethiopians kept attacking them and taking their land.

04:57.753 --> 04:59.856
So he was incredible.

04:59.916 --> 05:02.219
He was absolutely incredible.

05:03.621 --> 05:12.914
I find it really interesting that the Bible doesn't tell us those stories and Josephus has to tell us.

05:13.314 --> 05:15.057
And it makes me smile really.

05:15.137 --> 05:27.937
I used to read this sentence in Numbers 12, verse 3, which says, now Moses was a very humble man, more humble than anyone else on the face of the earth.

05:28.838 --> 05:30.981
And it made me smile.

05:31.062 --> 05:41.618
And I think about Hercule Poirot, when Hastings is trying to talk to him, trying to tell him he needs to be a bit more humble, because he always thought he was the best

05:42.146 --> 05:47.491
and detective in the whole world and you say, I am learning.

05:47.511 --> 05:51.515
I shall be the most humble person in the world.

05:52.096 --> 06:10.514
No one will match Hercule Poirot for his humbility and it just, it seems strange to me that these stories about Moses, about his greatness, his power and authority were not included in the Bible but then I think, well,

06:10.690 --> 06:20.405
Moses actually is a trip, the first five books that the Bible called the Pentateuch was mainly written by Moses.

06:20.566 --> 06:23.510
And actually, he never mentions these.

06:23.951 --> 06:27.516
So maybe he was really genuinely a humble person.

06:29.319 --> 06:36.370
So at the beginning of Exodus, we see Moses as a man who wanted to help his people.

06:36.511 --> 06:38.674
He had this inner connection

06:39.010 --> 06:45.400
with the Hebrews, and he hated to see them being treated so badly by their slave masters.

06:46.061 --> 06:49.326
And one day, his anger just got the better of him.

06:49.386 --> 06:58.341
And ultimately, he just killed the Egyptian who was threatening the Hebrew.

06:58.381 --> 07:01.245
He killed him, and I think crumbs.

07:01.866 --> 07:04.210
He must have been really strong, mustn't he?

07:04.610 --> 07:09.916
You know, to be able to do that, there's no mention of any problem in doing it.

07:10.076 --> 07:11.498
He killed the Egyptian.

07:14.121 --> 07:21.188
And this was one of those occasions where Moses' anger got the better of him.

07:21.269 --> 07:24.412
Moses was not a perfect person, just like us.

07:25.213 --> 07:33.362
And he had times where his anger got the better of him further on as he led the people later.

07:33.762 --> 07:38.649
Anyway, he thought that no one had seen him kill that Egyptian.

07:39.650 --> 07:47.281
But the next day he went out and there were two of his own people, Hebrews, fighting each other.

07:48.123 --> 07:52.068
And he says, come on guys, you are both Hebrews.

07:52.189 --> 07:54.091
Why are you doing this to each other?

07:54.111 --> 08:01.522
And they turn around and say to him, who's made you leader over us?

08:03.042 --> 08:07.389
Do you going to kill us like you killed the Egyptian?

08:07.409 --> 08:16.703
And suddenly Moses knew that he had been seen and that this would lead to quite serious action.

08:17.163 --> 08:18.565
So he runs away.

08:18.625 --> 08:23.913
And he goes into Midian.

08:23.933 --> 08:26.097
He becomes a shepherd.

08:26.217 --> 08:28.881
He marries a lady who's a shepherd.

08:29.562 --> 08:32.306
And he is there for 40

08:32.578 --> 08:35.301
years, 40 years.

08:38.225 --> 08:39.146
How incredible.

08:40.047 --> 08:49.059
This man who had so much potential and so much power spent 40 years of his life just looking after sheep.

08:50.481 --> 08:53.685
However, God had his hand on him.

08:54.065 --> 08:57.810
He'd had his hand on him right from the beginning and

08:58.210 --> 09:03.395
We probably all know the story of the burning bush, but I will just kind of refresh us.

09:04.356 --> 09:18.829
Moses was looking after the sheep and he goes out into the wilderness and he sees this bush that is on fire and he hears God speaking to him out of the bush.

09:19.890 --> 09:28.018
So when the Lord saw that he had gone over to look, God called to him from within the bush, Moses, Moses,

09:28.386 --> 09:30.368
And Moses said, here I am.

09:30.408 --> 09:33.672
Do not come any closer, God said.

09:33.712 --> 09:38.497
Take off your sandals for the place where your standing is holy ground.

09:39.378 --> 09:46.846
Then he said, I am the God of your father, the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob.

09:47.807 --> 09:52.472
At this, Moses hid his face because he was afraid to look at God.

09:53.693 --> 09:54.834
The Lord said,

09:54.914 --> 09:58.559
I have indeed seen the misery of my people in Egypt.

09:59.120 --> 10:05.348
I've heard them crying out because of their slave drivers, and I am concerned about their suffering.

10:05.629 --> 10:19.668
So I've come down to rescue them from the hand of the Egyptians and to bring them up out of that land into a good and spacious land, a land flowing with milk and honey, the home of all the Iats.

10:20.469 --> 10:21.010
Now,

10:21.218 --> 10:27.047
The cry of the Israelite has reached me, and I've seen the way the Egyptians are oppressing them.

10:27.648 --> 10:34.618
So now go, I am sending you to Pharaoh to bring my people the Israelites out of Egypt.

10:35.480 --> 10:43.191
But Moses said to God, who am I that I should go to Pharaoh and bring the Israelites out of Egypt?

10:43.792 --> 10:46.376
And God said, I will be with you.

10:46.396 --> 10:50.162
Amazing.

10:50.818 --> 10:53.882
that he had this encounter with God.

10:54.503 --> 11:07.861
Even more amazing was that he was being sent by God to do the most incredible miracles and wonders to bring the people out of Egypt into their promised land.

11:08.582 --> 11:12.547
And here he is saying, who am I?

11:12.567 --> 11:15.551
Who am I that I should do this?

11:18.455 --> 11:20.498
And he has at this stage

11:20.610 --> 11:24.974
You can sense that he has lost all his self-esteem.

11:25.755 --> 11:29.359
He's forgotten about the times when he led our an army.

11:29.799 --> 11:35.505
He's forgotten about the times when he was clever and knew a lot of things.

11:35.765 --> 11:37.767
And now he's going, who am I?

11:37.787 --> 11:48.978
And his low self-esteem could well have stopped him from stepping into the story that God had for him.

11:50.082 --> 11:55.229
But I feel like there's something else in that when he says, who am I?

11:55.309 --> 11:59.514
It's like he's lost his sense of identity.

11:59.554 --> 12:02.618
It's like he doesn't know who he is anymore.

12:03.319 --> 12:13.852
And when you think about it, he might kind of been saying, who am I, an Egyptian prince, a general in the Egyptian army?

12:13.872 --> 12:15.995
Am I a murderer?

12:16.496 --> 12:18.418
Because I killed that Egyptian.

12:18.722 --> 12:22.165
Am I a Hebrew or am I just a shepherd?

12:22.646 --> 12:25.148
He didn't know who he was.

12:26.189 --> 12:33.536
And I think that's another thing that can stop us from stepping into the story that God has for us, isn't it?

12:34.878 --> 12:41.064
And then he went on to other fears and excuses of why he couldn't do this.

12:41.524 --> 12:47.570
Chapter four verse one says, what if they don't believe me or listen to me?

12:48.290 --> 12:51.474
He's afraid that he will have a battle.

12:51.534 --> 12:53.737
He feels he can't do it.

12:53.777 --> 12:55.419
They're not going to respect him.

12:56.360 --> 12:59.204
And he has all this stuff going on in his head.

12:59.224 --> 13:03.409
And it could be the memories of killing the Egyptian.

13:03.470 --> 13:06.113
It could be all sorts of things.

13:06.714 --> 13:11.540
He was afraid that the people would not receive him as their leader.

13:13.603 --> 13:16.306
And so we read in Exodus 4,

13:16.450 --> 13:29.242
verses 10 to 13, Moses said to the Lord, pardon your servant, Lord, I have never been eloquent, neither in the past nor since you have spoken to your servant.

13:29.863 --> 13:31.924
I am slow of speech and tongue.

13:31.965 --> 13:36.429
The Lord said to him, who gave human beings their mouths?

13:36.569 --> 13:38.110
Who made them deaf or mute?

13:38.170 --> 13:40.893
Who gives them sight or makes them blind?

13:41.073 --> 13:42.534
Is it not I, the Lord?

13:42.574 --> 13:46.418
Now go, I will help you speak.

13:46.562 --> 13:48.144
and teach you what to say.

13:48.184 --> 13:54.691
But Moses said, pardon your servant Lord, please send someone else.

13:55.892 --> 13:57.674
I so relate to Moses.

13:57.714 --> 14:08.967
He had come to such a low point that he didn't think he could actually do what God had told him to do.

14:09.007 --> 14:15.314
And he's just saying, I really don't want the job.

14:15.682 --> 14:17.384
Lord, I don't want the job.

14:17.604 --> 14:18.845
I don't want to do it.

14:18.905 --> 14:22.909
I'm sure you could find someone else who would be a lot better.

14:23.309 --> 14:28.294
And he could have had other excuses that he didn't actually say at this time.

14:28.855 --> 14:35.181
I mean, the guy was 80 years old when he started this journey.

14:35.982 --> 14:36.883
I'm old, Lord.

14:37.003 --> 14:37.743
I'm tired.

14:37.763 --> 14:39.265
I don't want to do this.

14:40.346 --> 14:44.530
And there's so many things that could have stopped him.

14:44.962 --> 14:48.948
from stepping into the story that God had for him.

14:48.988 --> 15:05.473
And to be fair to him, when he did take the job on, he had endless difficulties, frustrations, things going wrong, people blaming him for taking them out there, asking, where can they get water from?

15:05.533 --> 15:11.101
One particular time, they said, oh, you shouldn't have brought us out of Egypt.

15:11.542 --> 15:13.404
We had meat to eat in Egypt.

15:13.464 --> 15:14.546
We want meat.

15:14.882 --> 15:17.766
We want meat and poor Moses.

15:18.227 --> 15:19.869
There's this whole bit in numbers.

15:20.650 --> 15:21.832
I will read this to you.

15:21.852 --> 15:24.896
I know time's a bit short, but I will read this.

15:25.356 --> 15:28.461
Numbers 11, 10 to 15.

15:28.541 --> 15:32.386
This is a conversation that Moses has with God.

15:33.708 --> 15:39.155
Moses heard the people of every family wailing at the entrance to their tents.

15:39.856 --> 15:43.922
The Lord became exceedingly angry and Moses was troubled.

15:44.290 --> 15:49.277
He asked the Lord, why have you brought this trouble on your servant?

15:49.738 --> 15:55.166
What have I done to displease you that you have put the burden of all these people on me?

15:55.726 --> 15:57.689
Did I conceive these people?

15:58.050 --> 15:59.432
Did I give them birth?

15:59.832 --> 16:02.456
Why do you tell me to carry them in my arms?

16:02.957 --> 16:09.146
And he goes on, he has a real old moan about the situation that he's having to face at that time.

16:09.726 --> 16:12.210
It was difficult.

16:13.186 --> 16:14.548
It was difficult.

16:16.269 --> 16:26.481
And sometimes he wanted to just pack up and go and leave that job and give them all back to God and just have a nice life.

16:28.764 --> 16:31.306
And we're like that, frankly, aren't we?

16:32.608 --> 16:41.618
So how did Moses, what made Moses the person that he really was, the person

16:41.794 --> 16:43.416
that God saw him to be.

16:43.476 --> 16:52.608
What made him that person was his passion for God, his passion to be in the presence of God, to spend time with God.

16:53.088 --> 16:57.033
And we see this so beautifully in Exodus 33.

16:58.355 --> 17:07.186
And it says, now Moses used to take a tent and pitch it outside the camp some distance away calling it the tent of meeting.

17:07.746 --> 17:12.371
Anyone inquiring of the Lord would go to the tent of meeting outside the camp.

17:12.431 --> 17:21.481
And whenever Moses went to the tent, the people rose and stood at the entrance to their tents, watching Moses until he entered the tent.

17:22.642 --> 17:30.130
As Moses went into the tent, the pillar of cloud would come down and stay at the entrance while the Lord spoke with Moses.

17:31.051 --> 17:37.458
Whenever the people saw the pillar of clouds standing at the entrance to the tent, they all stood up worshiped.

17:37.858 --> 17:40.141
each at the entrance to their tent.

17:40.882 --> 17:46.529
The Lord would speak to Moses face to face as one speaks to a friend.

17:48.031 --> 17:56.762
And Moses said to the Lord, you have been telling me, lead these people, but you have not let me know whom you will send with me.

17:57.522 --> 18:02.569
You have said, I know you by name and you have found favor with me.

18:02.609 --> 18:06.834
If you are pleased with me, teach me,

18:07.074 --> 18:16.544
your ways so that I may know you and continue to find favor with you.

18:17.285 --> 18:20.529
Remember that this nation is your people.

18:21.470 --> 18:27.356
The Lord replied, my presence will go with you and I will give you rest.

18:27.897 --> 18:36.146
And Moses said to him, if your presence does not go with us, do not send us up from here.

18:37.026 --> 18:41.931
His heart was so much for the presence of God.

18:41.972 --> 18:52.944
And that's what caused him to step into this difficult story at a difficult time, face those challenges and overcome them.

18:56.067 --> 18:58.890
The amazing thing was his heart for God.

18:58.930 --> 19:01.874
He had such a heart for God.

19:02.715 --> 19:05.778
He used to love to spend time in God's presence

19:06.082 --> 19:08.004
He went up the mountain one time.

19:08.044 --> 19:10.908
He was there for 40 days and 40 nights.

19:12.249 --> 19:13.951
Wow, what a man.

19:19.758 --> 19:24.103
Bill Johnson writes in his book, Face to Face with God.

19:25.705 --> 19:33.394
Moses was hungry for God alone, not merely for what God could do to make him successful.

19:34.178 --> 19:43.888
He insisted on following the presence of God himself, saying, if your presence does not go with us, do not lead us up from here.

19:45.089 --> 19:54.559
Moses was the great leader he was because he was not focused on personal success, but on the God who could be known.

19:55.480 --> 20:01.746
Moses preferred the wilderness with God to the promised land without God.

20:03.938 --> 20:07.622
Do you know you and I, we can make excuses.

20:08.984 --> 20:19.535
All the excuses we like for not fully following the plan that God has for us, for not fully stepping into the story he has for us.

20:20.636 --> 20:29.586
Or we can choose like Moses to lay those excuses down and focus on God himself.

20:31.010 --> 20:43.123
If we make his presence our aim and chief joy in life, there will be no limit what he can do in us and through us.

20:44.745 --> 20:52.914
The thing that stops most of us from stepping fully into this plans and story that God has for us is our own self.

20:54.115 --> 20:56.498
We are all basically selfish.

20:56.898 --> 21:03.389
We all want to be free from burdens and stress and people and difficulties.

21:05.472 --> 21:07.035
It's hard sometimes.

21:07.596 --> 21:20.176
The challenges we face, and I know, Pete and Nikki, they have a lot of challenges in leading this church and the network, but they have chosen to make God their focus.

21:20.737 --> 21:23.602
They are worshipers, first and foremost.

21:23.874 --> 21:29.383
And I hope that that is all of our hearts as we sit under their leadership.

21:31.246 --> 21:40.881
There are some very challenging verses in the Bible that we prefer not to talk about, but they are then on the left.

21:42.103 --> 21:52.018
And Jesus said, if you're going to follow me, you can't love your father or your mother or your parents, your children,

21:52.738 --> 21:54.801
I have to be number one.

21:54.841 --> 21:56.783
I have to be number one.

21:56.803 --> 22:03.251
He says, whoever does not take up their cross and follow me is not worthy of me.

22:05.113 --> 22:12.282
Whoever finds their life will lose it and whoever loses their life, for my sake will find it.

22:15.145 --> 22:19.090
We're not actually called to have a comfortable life.

22:20.098 --> 22:22.722
we are called to do whatever God tells us to do.

22:24.065 --> 22:29.073
Like Moses, we might not think that's what we want to do initially.

22:30.115 --> 22:46.642
But if we will say yes to God, if we will spend time in His presence as of the first priority in our lives, if we will listen to Him, and if we will not make all the excuses

22:48.546 --> 22:54.034
same we're too tired, too old, too this, too that, whatever.

22:54.836 --> 23:01.285
Who knows what God could do with us if we're willing to lie, lay our lives down?

23:01.386 --> 23:10.059
If we're willing to let God, as He did with Moses, take us to a place where it's not going to be about us.

23:10.660 --> 23:13.404
It's all going to be about God and His glory.

23:14.105 --> 23:17.330
He wants to empty us of ourselves.

23:17.666 --> 23:26.540
so that we can be so full of God, that we can carry his presence wherever we go and make a difference.

23:28.243 --> 23:45.490
Smith Wigglesworth said, the striking thing about Moses is that it took him 40 years to learn human wisdom, 40 years to know his helplessness, and 40 years to live in the power of God.

23:46.562 --> 23:51.469
FB Maya in his wonderful book about Moses says, and what is this faith?

23:52.591 --> 24:03.327
Is it not some inherent power or quality in certain men by virtue of which they are able to accomplish special results unrealized by others?

24:04.408 --> 24:13.842
It is rather the power of putting self aside that God may work unhindered through nature.

24:14.722 --> 24:17.385
God cannot give his glory to another.

24:17.485 --> 24:24.953
He dare not trust his power to men till they are humbled and emptied and conscious of their helplessness.

24:25.934 --> 24:29.278
Even the sun learned obedience through what he suffered.

24:30.199 --> 24:35.986
You must be brought to an end of yourself before God can begin with you.

24:37.027 --> 24:43.474
But when once you have come to that point, there is no limit to what can be wrought

24:44.290 --> 24:51.418
during a single life by the passage through it of his eternal power and Godhead.

24:55.042 --> 25:05.493
I really used to love listening when I was a student to Andrei Crouch and the disciples, and they had some beautiful songs, but there was one.

25:05.533 --> 25:10.398
And it said, all to Jesus, I surrender.

25:11.840 --> 25:13.842
All to him I freely gave.

25:14.338 --> 25:19.584
I will ever love and trust him in his presence daily live.

25:19.644 --> 25:22.187
I surrender all.

25:23.349 --> 25:24.450
I surrender all.

25:25.672 --> 25:26.753
All to Jesus.

25:27.634 --> 25:28.535
I surrender.

25:29.496 --> 25:30.657
I surrender all."

25:32.380 --> 25:38.086
And another song said, all that I am and ever hope to be.

25:38.106 --> 25:41.170
I owe it all to thee.

25:42.658 --> 25:45.281
Last week Pete was talking about giving.

25:46.142 --> 25:50.367
And there's a beautiful verse in 2 Corinthians 8 verse 5.

25:50.487 --> 25:58.556
And Paul is writing to the church in Corinth and telling them about the extreme generosity of the Macedonians.

25:59.036 --> 26:03.401
And he said, they gave as much as they were able.

26:04.242 --> 26:09.308
And even beyond their ability, they exceeded our expectations.

26:09.888 --> 26:11.570
They gave themselves.

26:12.162 --> 26:15.407
First of all to the Lord.

26:15.447 --> 26:20.815
Today, I just feel like this is giving Sunday.

26:20.855 --> 26:25.141
Have we given all of ourself to God?

26:26.163 --> 26:28.106
God wants us to do that.

26:28.566 --> 26:41.746
We can be so incredibly blessed if we would just step out of our comfort zone and just follow what He tells us to do, what He shows us to do, the things He lays on our hearts.

26:42.402 --> 26:53.333
I feel like he just wants us to give our whole self to him this morning, not holding anything back, but just say, God, here I am.

26:53.433 --> 26:58.758
You gave everything for me, and I want to give everything for you.

26:58.778 --> 27:09.108
I also feel like God wants to help us when we get to that place, when we say, who am I, Lord?

27:10.069 --> 27:11.090
Who am I?

27:12.706 --> 27:17.073
We can put ourselves down and we can make ourselves too big.

27:18.275 --> 27:19.577
But who am I?

27:19.617 --> 27:24.244
How does God see each one of us?

27:24.484 --> 27:26.427
We all have unique gifts.

27:26.548 --> 27:29.893
We all have unique abilities that God has put in us.

27:31.115 --> 27:33.418
We need Him to show us those things.

27:34.300 --> 27:35.301
Who am I?

27:38.186 --> 27:40.850
But there's another aspect as well.

27:41.762 --> 27:46.790
We need to know who God says we are from his word.

27:47.732 --> 28:02.797
When Jesus started his ministry just before he was baptized and he heard these words spoken over him, this is my son whom I love and with him I am well pleased.

28:03.939 --> 28:07.986
At that point Jesus has done nothing apart from carpentry.

28:10.754 --> 28:17.204
When we know that we are God's child, we are made in his image.

28:17.865 --> 28:21.210
There's no mistakes in the way he put us together.

28:21.290 --> 28:22.431
We're all unique.

28:23.052 --> 28:38.135
When we know that we are his, his chosen child, his chosen person, we can carry his presence with us in whatever we do.

28:38.155 --> 28:40.178
We can know

28:40.322 --> 28:41.924
that he is pleased with us.

28:42.724 --> 28:49.891
He says that over each of us, not because of great things we've done already.

28:49.911 --> 28:53.695
He says that because he loves us.

28:54.916 --> 29:01.142
And everything in our past does not have to determine where we will end up.

29:01.362 --> 29:02.464
Look at Moses.

29:02.724 --> 29:04.085
He wasn't perfect.

29:04.185 --> 29:07.588
He had a hard time, had a difficult childhood.

29:07.709 --> 29:09.170
I don't know how he coped.

29:09.282 --> 29:20.915
knowing that he's been brought up as a prince in this royal palace, but actually his real family were living in probably poverty and squalor.

29:21.996 --> 29:23.258
How did he cope with that?

29:27.162 --> 29:34.090
But God sees us in Christ, and he sees Christ in us.

29:34.911 --> 29:38.034
He has put his spirit in us.

29:38.818 --> 29:42.503
We are all new creations when we come to Him.

29:42.564 --> 29:44.506
The old has gone.

29:44.547 --> 29:46.489
The new has come.

29:47.150 --> 29:48.452
Let God show you.

29:48.512 --> 29:52.278
Let Him show you who He has made you to be.

29:52.298 --> 30:01.111
And when you know who you are, you will find the path that He has marked out for you.

30:01.191 --> 30:08.402
You will be able to step into the story that He has specifically for you.

30:10.114 --> 30:13.640
God loves us so, so much.

30:14.341 --> 30:17.907
And he wants to develop his character in us.

30:18.808 --> 30:21.092
He wants to make us like Jesus.

30:22.154 --> 30:24.458
But the journey is not always easy.

30:24.478 --> 30:27.042
I'm not going to stand up here and lie to you.

30:27.062 --> 30:31.890
The journey of becoming like Jesus.

30:32.386 --> 30:40.596
where all our faults and failures he gently shows us and he gently teaches us how to become more like Jesus.

30:41.417 --> 30:43.078
We are his children.

30:43.839 --> 30:47.283
He has got plans for each one of you in this room.

30:47.323 --> 30:51.989
Don't ever say, I'm only or just.

30:53.370 --> 30:55.933
Always say, I am a child of God.

30:56.414 --> 30:59.858
He loves me and he is pleased with me.

31:00.418 --> 31:06.183
and he wants the very, very best for me, even though it might be a painful journey.

31:07.084 --> 31:12.149
God has got so much that he wants to do with each one of you.

31:12.169 --> 31:30.066
I just pray that you will know who he says you are and that you will go out giving your whole self to him today and just take off yourself, all those labels that people have put on you over the years.

31:30.402 --> 31:34.909
Maybe things that are even good about you, but you don't feel comfortable with them.

31:34.949 --> 31:36.672
It doesn't feel like your heart.

31:37.834 --> 31:43.683
Some people have been trapped by things others have said over them.

31:43.923 --> 31:48.170
I had a friend and she kept telling me how shy she was.

31:48.210 --> 31:58.386
And I kept thinking I don't see really a shy person here, but I didn't know what to say, so I didn't.

31:59.202 --> 32:06.211
At some point, she realized that that label had been stuck on her from an early age.

32:07.093 --> 32:12.220
And actually, although it had been true back then, it wasn't true anymore.

32:12.941 --> 32:19.389
And once she took that label off herself, she was able to train and become a Baptist minister.

32:20.991 --> 32:23.895
What is holding you back today?

32:25.017 --> 32:26.559
What holds us back?

32:26.839 --> 32:28.882
Is it the things people have said?

32:30.210 --> 32:34.135
Is it our own self-esteem, our own picture of ourself?

32:35.536 --> 32:37.499
Let's put all that down today.

32:37.519 --> 32:48.431
And if you need to take some labels off yourself so you can move forward and be all that God has made you to be, we have an amazing prayer team.

32:48.531 --> 32:57.522
I'm sure they would love to pray those things off you and help you to get free and see yourself as God sees you.

32:58.626 --> 33:04.475
Each one of you is so loved and each so precious and each so unique.

33:05.497 --> 33:07.861
Never compare yourself to someone else.

33:08.702 --> 33:15.052
Be the true person that God has made you to be and who knows what God will do with you.

33:15.713 --> 33:16.354
Let's pray.

33:16.414 --> 33:26.450
Lord God, we thank you so much that you love us so much, that you have good plans for us.

33:27.426 --> 33:30.491
Lord, that you see beyond the labels.

33:30.591 --> 33:34.998
You see beyond what people have said over us over the years.

33:35.679 --> 33:37.822
You see us as you made us.

33:38.924 --> 33:54.208
Lord, I just pray that each person here this morning will be able to leave their labels behind, leave their past behind and step into the stories that you have for them in Jesus' name.

33:54.248 --> 33:55.570
Amen.

